But many homeowners only see dollar signs, and are unpleasantly surprised when they realize how much it actually costs to sell their home.
Let’s go over a few of the hidden costs of selling a home that can take homeowners by surprise.
The seller will likely ask for concessions— for example, splitting or paying the inspection fees, closing costs, or processing fees.
Real Estate CommissionYou’ve heard a lot about this expense, and most of it is probably true; real estate commissions usually come to a whopping 5% to 6% of the sale price.
